            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Jeremiah.22:1-23:20",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJeremiah%2022%3A1-23%3A20%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_1%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJeremiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EA%20Message%20for%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Kings%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20me%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BGo%20over%20and%20speak%20directly%20to%20the%20king%20of%20Judah.%20Say%20to%20him%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_2%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2018%3BListen%20to%20this%20message%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20you%20king%20of%20Judah%2C%20sitting%20on%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20throne.%20Let%20your%20attendants%20and%20your%20people%20listen%2C%20too.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_3%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20Be%20fair-minded%20and%20just.%20Do%20what%20is%20right!%20Help%20those%20who%20have%20been%20robbed%3B%20rescue%20them%20from%20their%20oppressors.%20Quit%20your%20evil%20deeds!%20Do%20not%20mistreat%20foreigners%2C%20orphans%2C%20and%20widows.%20Stop%20murdering%20the%20innocent!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_4%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EIf%20you%20obey%20me%2C%20there%20will%20always%20be%20a%20descendant%20of%20David%20sitting%20on%20the%20throne%20here%20in%20Jerusalem.%20The%20king%20will%20ride%20through%20the%20palace%20gates%20in%20chariots%20and%20on%20horses%2C%20with%20his%20parade%20of%20attendants%20and%20subjects.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_5%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20if%20you%20refuse%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20this%20warning%2C%20I%20swear%20by%20my%20own%20name%2C%20says%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20that%20this%20palace%20will%20become%20a%20pile%20of%20rubble.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_6%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EA%20Message%20about%20the%20Palace%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20this%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%20concerning%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20royal%20palace%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20love%20you%20as%20much%20as%20fruitful%20Gilead%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20the%20green%20forests%20of%20Lebanon.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EBut%20I%20will%20turn%20you%20into%20a%20desert%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ewith%20no%20one%20living%20within%20your%20walls.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_7%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20will%20call%20for%20wreckers%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ewho%20will%20bring%20out%20their%20tools%20to%20dismantle%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThey%20will%20tear%20out%20all%20your%20fine%20cedar%20beams%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20throw%20them%20on%20the%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_8%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BPeople%20from%20many%20nations%20will%20pass%20by%20the%20ruins%20of%20this%20city%20and%20say%20to%20one%20another%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWhy%20did%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20destroy%20such%20a%20great%20city%3F%26%23x2019%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_9%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20the%20answer%20will%20be%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BBecause%20they%20violated%20their%20covenant%20with%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20their%20God%20by%20worshiping%20other%20gods.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_10%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EA%20Message%20about%20Jehoahaz%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EDo%20not%20weep%20for%20the%20dead%20king%20or%20mourn%20his%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3EInstead%2C%20weep%20for%20the%20captive%20king%20being%20led%20away!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3EFor%20he%20will%20never%20return%20to%20see%20his%20native%20land%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_22_11%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2222%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20this%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%20about%20Jehoahaz%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E22%3A11%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EShallum%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20another%20name%20for%20Jehoahaz.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20who%20succeeded%20his%20father%2C%20King%20Josiah%2C%20and%20wa